 for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ellen Broughton was born in 1213, in Merionethshire, Wales, her father, Hywel \"hir\" ap Gruffudd, was 29 and her mother, Gwenhwyfar ferch Gronwy, was 26. She had at least 5 sons and 1 daughter with Rhys ap Gruffudd."},"et":{"@1213–":"1213–Surnud","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1213–Female":"1213–Surnud","1215–Male":"1215–Surnud","1217–Male":"1217–Surnud","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1211–Male":"1211–Surnud","1231–Male":"1231–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1185–Male":"1185–Surnud","1188–Female":"1188–Surnud","1231":"1231","1230":"1230","1185":"1185","1217":"1217","1215":"1215","31 MAY 1956":"31. mai 1956","1213":"1213","1211":"1211","1188":"1188","1210":"1210","31 JAN 1956":"31. jaanuar 1956","16 NOV 1956":"16. november 1956","about 1231":"umbes 1231","@1213":"1213","of,Cantref Mawr, Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales","{Cdfr ap Gwthfd}":"Ascoli Piceno, Marche, Itaalia","Of, Tal-Y-Bont Cmt, Merionethshire, Wales":"Merionethshire, Wales"},"fi":{"@1213–":"1213–Kuollut","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1213–Female":"1213–Kuollut","1215–Male":"1215–Kuollut","1217–Male":"1217–Kuollut","1230–Female":"1230–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1211–Male":"1211–Kuollut","1231–Male":"1231–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1185–Male":"1185–Kuollut","118